<h2 id=3D"add-code-to-detect-language">Add code to detect language</h2>
<p>Now that you have created a client for the API, let's use it to detect t=
he language in which each review is written.</p>
<ol class=3D"taskList">
<li class=3D"task-list-item" id=3D"taskIndex23"><p><label class=3D"checkbox=
"><input type=3D"checkbox" aria-labelledby=3D"taskIndex23"><span></span></l=
abel>In the code editor, find the comment <strong>Get language</strong>. Th=
en add the code necessary to detect the language in each review document:</=
p>
<pre><div class=3D"codeTitle"><span class=3D"title">python</span><span clas=
s=3D"title"><span class=3D"type-code-block">Type</span><span class=3D"copy-=
code-block">Copy</span></span></div><code class=3D"python language-python p=
rettyprint prettyprinted" tabindex=3D"0" style=3D""><span class=3D"com"># G=
et language</span><span class=3D"pln">
detectedLanguage </span><span class=3D"pun">=3D</span><span class=3D"pln"> =
ai_client</span><span class=3D"pun">.</span><span class=3D"pln">detect_lang=
uage</span><span class=3D"pun">(</span><span class=3D"pln">documents</span>=
<span class=3D"pun">=3D[</span><span class=3D"pln">text</span><span class=
=3D"pun">])[</span><span class=3D"lit">0</span><span class=3D"pun">]</span>=
<span class=3D"pln">
</span><span class=3D"kwd">print</span><span class=3D"pun">(</span><span cl=
ass=3D"str">'\nLanguage: {}'</span><span class=3D"pun">.</span><span class=
=3D"pln">format</span><span class=3D"pun">(</span><span class=3D"pln">detec=
tedLanguage</span><span class=3D"pun">.</span><span class=3D"pln">primary_l=
anguage</span><span class=3D"pun">.</span><span class=3D"pln">name</span><s=
pan class=3D"pun">))</span></code></pre>
<blockquote>
  <p><strong>Note</strong>: <em>In this example, each review is analyzed in=
dividually, resulting in a separate call to the service for each file. An a=
